cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

This paper deals with the application of super-resolution techniques to satellite imagery and the effects of these techniques on object detection algorithm performance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for object detection, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with satellite imagery, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
